The paper presents a framework for demystification of convolutional deep learning models for time series analysis, which falls under the domain of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The framework focuses on visualization and interpretability of the deep learning models, which is a common theme in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of convolutional neural networks for time series analysis also suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also mentions the importance of understanding the network features for domains like finance, industry 4.0, self-driving cars, health-care, counter-terrorism, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of pruning filters without significant loss in performance, which suggests the possibility of the paper belonging to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
